ZH: 他常常说谎话，所以没人相信他。
EN: He often tells lies, so nobody believes him.

ZH: 她向老师说了一个谎话以逃避罚款。
EN: She told a lie to the teacher to avoid getting fined.

ZH: 我们应该克制自己，不要撒谎话。
EN: We should control ourselves and not tell lies.

ZH: 这个小孩容易说谎话，必须多加教导。
EN: This child tends to tell lies easily, he needs more guidance.

ZH: 我们要相信自己的孩子，不要轻易怀疑他们说谎话。
EN: We should trust our children and not easily doubt if they are lying.

ZH: 他说了个谎话，当场就被揭穿了。
EN: He told a lie and was exposed on the spot.

ZH: 谎话终究要被揭露。
EN: Lies will eventually be exposed.

ZH: 我意识到他一直在对我撒谎话。
EN: I realized that he had been lying to me all along.

ZH: 她为了保护自己不得不说谎话。
EN: She had to tell a lie to protect herself.

ZH: 我们应该告诉孩子说实话比撒谎话更重要。
EN: We should teach children that telling the truth is more important than lying.

ZH: 别人的谎话不会给你带来好处。
EN: Other people's lies won't bring you any benefits.

ZH: 她的谎话让她失去了信任。
EN: Her lies made her lose trust.

ZH: 虽然他说了谎话，但是我还是原谅了他。
EN: Although he told a lie, I still forgave him.

ZH: 对方的谎话让我感到很失望。
EN: I felt very disappointed by the other person's lie.

ZH: 在任何情况下都不应该撒谎话。
EN: You should never tell lies under any circumstances.

ZH: 如果你撒了谎话，你会后悔的。
EN: If you tell a lie, you will regret it.

ZH: 虽然撒谎话可能暂时受益，但是最终会被揭穿。
EN: Although telling lies may bring temporary benefits, they will eventually be exposed.

ZH: 他的谎话伤害了很多人的感情。
EN: His lies hurt the feelings of many people.

ZH: 我不喜欢和爱撒谎话的人打交道。
EN: I don't like dealing with people who tell lies.

ZH: 我们不能容忍谁撒谎话。
EN: We cannot tolerate anyone who tells lies.

ZH: 幸福建立在诚实上，而不是谎话之中。
EN: Happiness is built on honesty, not on lies.
